UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2551
1 years due to the improved working conditions in mines across eastern Kentucky and
2 throughout the United States;
3 NOW, THEREFORE,
4 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
5 Kentucky:
6 Section 1. The members of the Senate hereby recognize the 50th anniversary of
7 the Scotia Mine Disaster in Letcher County, and honor the memory of the 26 lives lost,
8 and the legacy of improved mine safety they leave even to this day.
9 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in honor of the 26
10 victims, their families, and the rescuers of the Scotia Mine Disaster of 1976.
11 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
12 Resolution to Senator Scott Madon.
